m-Jim War?|journal=Review of Culture 18 (1994)|p=20\u201324}}\n* {{citation|last=Niderost|first=Eric|title=Turtleboat Destiny: The Imjin War and Yi Sun Shin|journal=Military Heritage |volume=2 |issue=6 |date=June 2001|p=50\u201359, 89}}\n* {{citation|last=Niderost|first=Eric|title=The Miracle at Myongnyang, 1597|journal=Osprey Military Journal |volume=4 |issue=1 |date=January 2002|p=44\u201350}}\n* {{citation|last=Park|first=Yune-hee|year=1973|title=Admiral Yi Sun-shin and His Turtleboat Armada: A Comprehensive Account of the Resistance of Korea to the 16th Century Japanese Invasion|publisher=Shinsaeng Press}}\n* {{citation|last=Rockstein|first=Edward D.|year=1993|title=Strategic And Operational Aspects of Japan's Invasions of Korea 1592\u20131598 1993-6-18|publisher=Naval War College}}\n* {{citation|last=Sadler|first=A. L.|title=The Naval Campaign in the Korean War of Hideyoshi (1592\u20131598)|journal=Transactions of the Asiatic Society of Japan |series=Second Series |volume=14 |date=June 1937|p=179\u2013208}}\n* {{citation|last=Sansom|first=George|year=1961|title=A History of Japan 1334\u20131615|publisher=Stanford University Press|isbn=978-0-8047-0525-7}}\n* {{citation|last=Sohn|first=Pow-key|title=Early Korean Painting|journal=Journal of the American Oriental Society |volume=79 |issue=2 |date=April\u2013June 1959|p=96\u2013103 |jstor=595851}}\n* {{citation|last=Stramigioli|first=Giuliana|title=Hideyoshi's Expansionist Policy on the Asiatic Mainland|journal=Transactions of the Asiatic Society of Japan |series=Third Series |volume=3 |date=December 1954|p=74\u2013116}}\n* {{citation|last=Strauss|first=Barry|title=Korea's Legendary Admiral|journal=MHQ: The Quarterly Journal of Military History |date=Summer 2005 |volume=17 |issue=4|p=52\u201361}}\n* {{citation|last=Swope|first=Kenneth M.|year=2006|title=Beyond Turtleboats: Siege Accounts from Hideyoshi's Second Invasion of Korea, 1597\u20131598|journal=Sungkyun Journal of East Asian Studies |volume=6 |issue=2 |publi