ai]] reported its first death, an 88-year-old man.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/shanghai-reports-first-death-from-china-coronavirus-2169790|title=Shanghai Reports First Death From China Coronavirus|website=NDTV.com|access-date=2020-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126035200/https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/shanghai-reports-first-death-from-china-coronavirus-2169790|archive-date=2020-01-26|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe United States confirmed its third, fourth, and fifth cases: two in [[California]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbclosangeles.com/news/los-angeles-countys-first-case-of-deadly-novel-coronavirus-confirmed/2298402/|title=Los Angeles County's First Case of Deadly Novel Coronavirus Confirmed|website=NBC Los Angeles|access-date=2020-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126191938/https://www.nbclosangeles.com/news/los-angeles-countys-first-case-of-deadly-novel-coronavirus-confirmed/2298402/|archive-date=2020-01-26|url-status=live}}</ref> and one in [[Arizona]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/summary.html|title=Novel Coronavirus 2019 Situation Summary, Wuhan, China &#124; CDC|date=29 January 2020|website=www.cdc.gov|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126210549/https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-nCoV/summary.html|archive-date=26 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Macau confirmed three additional cases, bringing its total to five.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://macaunews.mo/government-confirms-5-cases-of-coronavirus-so-far-in-macau/|title=Government confirms 5 cases of coronavirus so far in Macau|date=2020-01-26|website=Macau News|access-date=2020-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126102217/https://macaunews.mo/government-confirms-5-cases-of-coronavirus-so-far-in-macau/|archive-date=2020-01-26|url-status=live}}</ref> Hong Kong confirmed its sixth, seventh, and eighth cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://amp.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/health-environment/article/3047689/china-coronavirus-hong-kong-has-its-sixth-patient|title=China coronavirus-Hong Kong's sixth patient|date=2020-01-26|website=South China Morning Post}}</ref> Thailand has confirmed its eighth case. The first of five patients was already discharged. There are another 39 suspected cases awaiting confirmation.<ref name=\"Thailand26Jan2020\">{{cite news|url=https://www.pptvhd36.com/news/\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e40\u0e14\u0e47\u0e19\u0e23\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e19/118387|title=\u0e2a\u0e18.\u0e22\u0e37\u0e19\u0e22\u0e31\u0e19\u0e1e\u0e1a\u0e1c\u0e39\u0e49\u0e1b\u0e48\u0e27\u0e22 \"\u0e44\u0e27\u0e23\u0e31\u0e2a\u0e42\u0e04\u0e42\u0e23\u0e19\u0e32\" 8 \u0e23\u0e32\u0e22|date=25 January 2020|accessdate=26 January 2020|language=th|website=PPTVHD36}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention]] (CCDC) has started developing vaccines against the coronavirus, an official with the center said on Sunday.<ref name=\":8\">{{cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/society/article/3047676/number-coronavirus-cases-china-doubles-spread-rate-accelerates|title=Chinese scientists race to develop vaccine as coronavirus death toll jumps|date=2020-01-26|website=SCMP|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126073453/https://www.scmp.com/news/china/society/article/3047676/number-coronavirus-cases-china-doubles-spread-rate-accelerates|archive-date=2020-01-26|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"xinhua_vacc\">{{cite web|url=http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2020-01/26/c_138734908.htm|title=China CDC developing novel coronavirus vaccine|date=2020-01-26|website=Xinhua|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126201658/http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2020-01/26/c_138734908.htm|archive-date=2020-01-26|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nHealth officials in Ivory Coast are dealing with a suspected case of coronavirus, the country's health ministry has announced.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-51258014|title=Ivory Coast fears China virus has reached Africa|date=2020-01-26|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128004440/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-51258014|archive-date=2020-01-28|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe United Nation's [[World Health Organization|WHO]] Director-General [[Tedros Adhanom|Tedros Ghebreyesus]] said he was on his way to Beijing to confer with Chinese officials and health experts about the coronavirus outbreak.<ref name=\"reuters26jan\">{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-who-idUSKBN1ZP0OG|title=WHO chief says he is on way to China to confer on virus, boost response|date=2020-01-26|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126185333/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-who-idUSKBN1ZP0OG|archive-date=2020-01-26|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nChina started requiring nationwide use of monitoring stations for screening, identification and immediate isolation of coronavirus-infected travellers, including at airports, railway stations, bus stations and ports.<ref name=\"china_measures\">{{cite web|url=https://news.yahoo.com/china-orders-nationwide-measures-detect-virus-flights-trains-090541811.html|title=China orders nationwide measures to detect virus on flights, trains, buses|website=news.yahoo.com|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126235511/https://news.yahoo.com/china-orders-nationwide-measures-detect-virus-flights-trains-090541811.html|archive-date=2020-01-26|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nA [https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/01/26/2019-ncov-china-epidemic-pandemic-the-wuhan-coronavirus-a-tentative-clinical-profile tentative clinical profile for the new coronavirus (2019-nCoV)] was published by an assistant professor of population health science at the [[Icahn School of Medicine at Mount Sinai]] in New York. The lethality of the virus is unknown; however, the death toll has now climbed to above three percent.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/01/26/2019-ncov-china-epidemic-pandemic-the-wuhan-coronavirus-a-tentative-clinical-profile/|title=How China's Coronavirus Is Spreading\u2014and How to Stop It|first=Annie|last=Sparrow|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131025848/https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/01/26/2019-ncov-china-epidemic-pandemic-the-wuhan-coronavirus-a-tentative-clinical-profile/|archive-date=2020-01-31|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nWang Xianliang, a Hubei provincial government official, died of pneumonia caused by the virus.<ref name=\"Radio Free Asia\"/>\n\n===27 January===\n'''WHO''' Situation Report 7:<ref>{{Citation|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200127-sitrep-7-2019--ncov.pdf?sfvrsn=98ef79f5_2|title=Novel Coronavirus(2019-nCoV) Situation Report - 7|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131215148/https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200127-sitrep-7-2019--ncov.pdf?sfvrsn=98ef79f5_2|archive-date=2020-01-31|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nGabriel Leung, Dean of the University of Hong Kong medical school and one of the foremost world experts on SARS and viruses, gave a three-hour presentation published on YouTube wherein he made nowcasts and forecasts of the coronavirus. Using traditional scientific modeling techniques that predict the spread of viruses, Leung projected the true number of coronavirus infections was likely 10 time more than the official reported numbers.<ref>{{Citation|title=Dr Gabriel Leung Dean of Medicine dire projection|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CwXMPsbxFfo|language=en|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201190644/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CwXMPsbxFfo|archive-date=2020-02-01|url-status=live}}</ref> Leung estimated that there were between 44,000\u2013100,000 infections in China as of 24 January 2020. He stated that draconian measures were needed to slow the progress of the virus but that these measures would have no effect in stopping the coronavirus pandemic. He projected that the number of infections would continue exponentially peaking out in late April or May 2020. Leung predicted that at the peak of the pandemic, there could be up to 100,000 new infections per day. Leung subsequently published an article in The Lancet nowcasting and forecasting the likely progression of the Wuhan coronavirus taking into consideration numerous variables.<ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://www.thelancet.com/journals/lancet/article/PIIS0140-6736(20)30260-9/abstract|title=Nowcasting and forecasting the potential domestic and international spread of the 2019-nCoV outbreak originating in Wuhan, China: a modelling study|first1=Joseph T.|last1=Wu|first2=Kathy|last2=Leung|first3=Gabriel M.|last3=Leung|date=31 January 2020|journal=The Lancet|volume=0|issue=10225|pages=689\u2013697|doi=10.1016/S0140-6736(20)30260-9|pmid=32014114|doi-access=free}}</ref>\nZhou Xianwang, the mayor of Wuhan, said on a Chinese state television talkshow that rules imposed by Beijing limited what he could disclose about the threat posed by the Wuhan coronavirus as it unfolded, suggesting \"the central government was partially responsible for a lack of transparency that has marred the response to the fast-expanding health crisis.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-premier-tours-virus-epicenter-as-anger-bubbles-at-crisis-response-11580109098|title=Wuhan Mayor Says Beijing Rules Partially Responsible for Lack of Transparency|first=Josh|last=Chin|date=28 January 2020|via=www.wsj.com|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200207052922/https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-premier-tours-virus-epicenter-as-anger-bubbles-at-crisis-response-11580109098|archive-date=7 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nCanada reported its first confirmed case and another presumptive case.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.ontario.ca/mohltc/en/2020/01/ontario-confirms-second-presumptive-case-of-wuhan-novel-coronavirus.html|title=Ontario Confirms Second Presumptive Case of Wuhan Novel Coronavirus|date=2020-01-27|work=Queen's Printer for Ontario|access-date=2020-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127133734/https://news.ontario.ca/mohltc/en/2020/01/ontario-confirms-second-presumptive-case-of-wuhan-novel-coronavirus.html|archive-date=2020-01-27|url-status=live}}</ref> Health officials have confirmed the fifth case of coronavirus in Australia, and have suspected an additional 5.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://7news.com.au/lifestyle/health-wellbeing/coronavirus-confirmed-fifth-australian-case-21-year-old-infected-with-deadly-virus--c-666385|title=Australia's fifth coronavirus case confirmed as death toll rises|date=2020-01-27|website=7NEWS.com.au|access-date=2020-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127045226/https://7news.com.au/lifestyle/health-wellbeing/coronavirus-confirmed-fifth-australian-case-21-year-old-infected-with-deadly-virus--c-666385|archive-date=2020-01-27|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theaustralian.com.au/subscribe/news/1/?sourceCode=TAWEB_WRE170_a&dest=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theaustralian.com.au%2Fworld%2Fchinas-president-xi-warns-of-grave-situation-as-coronavirus-spreads%2Fnews-story%2F1ec90ec8471e5cc18f2cb44c6189ad33&memtype=anonymous&mode=premium&nk=b667d400f3332cebc3e2cd253c3853fe-1580102429|title=Subscribe to The Australian|website=www.theaustralian.com.au|access-date=2020-01-27}}</ref> The Sri Lankan Health Ministry confirms its first case of coronavirus, a 43 year old Chinese woman.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.adaderana.lk/news/60461/chinese-female-at-idh-tests-positive-for-coronavirus|title=First confirmed case of Coronavirus reported in Sri Lanka|website=adaderana.lk|access-date=2020-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127154649/http://www.adaderana.lk/news/60461/chinese-female-at-idh-tests-positive-for-coronavirus|archive-date=2020-01-27|url-status=live}}</ref> Cambodia confirms its first case of the virus, a Chinese man who came with his family to [[Sihanoukville (city)|Sihanoukville]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-01-28/coronavirus-claims-first-life-in-beijing/11904622|title=Coronavirus claims first life in China's capital, as global spread continues|date=2020-01-28|website=ABC News|language=en-AU|access-date=2020-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128012345/https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-01-28/coronavirus-claims-first-life-in-beijing/11904622|archive-date=2020-01-28|url-status=live}}</ref> Singapore confirms a fifth case, a 56 year old Chinese national who arrived from Wuhan on 18 January.<ref name=\"ST28Jan\">{{cite news|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/wuhan-virus-singapore-confirms-5th-case-patient-from-wuhan-stayed-at-her-familys-home-in|title=Wuhan virus: Singapore confirms 5th case; patient from Wuhan stayed at her family's home in Ceylon Road|last1=Toh|first1=Yong Chuan|date=28 January 2020|work=The Straits Times|accessdate=28 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128003837/https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/wuhan-virus-singapore-confirms-5th-case-patient-from-wuhan-stayed-at-her-familys-home-in|archive-date=28 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Germany confirmed its first case in [[Bavaria]], a case of domestic transmission.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.spiegel.de/wissenschaft/medizin/corona-virus-erster-fall-in-deutschland-bestaetigt-a-19843b8d-8694-451f-baf7-0189d3356f99|title=Erster Fall des Coronavirus in Deutschland best\u00e4tigt|date=2020-01-28|language=de|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dw.com/en/germany-confirms-first-case-of-coronavirus/a-52169007|title=Germany confirms first case of coronavirus {{!}} DW {{!}} 27.01.2020|website=DW.COM|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-01-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128022332/https://www.dw.com/en/germany-confirms-first-case-of-coronavirus/a-52169007|archive-date=2020-01-28|url-status=live}}</ref> Taiwan reports its first case of domestic transmission of the coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/east-asia/wuhan-virus-taiwan-reports-first-case-of-domestic-coronavirus-transmission|title=Wuhan virus: Taiwan reports first case of domestic coronavirus transmission|date=28 January 2020|website=The Straits Times|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200207192737/https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/east-asia/wuhan-virus-taiwan-reports-first-case-of-domestic-coronavirus-transmission|archive-date=7 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[Beijing]] reports its first death from coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.france24.com/en/20200127-beijing-reports-capital-s-first-death-from-coronavirus|title=Beijing reports capital's first death from coronavirus|date=2020-01-27|website=France 24|language=en|access-date=2020-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127165028/https://www.france24.com/en/20200127-beijing-reports-capital-s-first-death-from-coronavirus|archive-date=2020-01-27|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThree new suspected cases in Austria; previous suspected cases tested negative.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.derstandard.at/story/2000113770946/gewissheit-zu-coronavirus-verdachtsfall-in-wien-erst-am-montag|title=Coronavirus: Zwei Personen negativ getestet, doch zwei neue Verdachtsf\u00e4lle|date=2020-01-27|work=derStandard|access-date=2020-01-27|language=de|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126221209/https://www.derstandard.at/story/2000113770946/gewissheit-zu-coronavirus-verdachtsfall-in-wien-erst-am-montag|archive-date=2020-01-26|url-status=live}}</ref> The '[[Matei Bal\u0219]]' Institute reported the first possible case in Romania.,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/posibil-caz-de-coronavirus-in-romania-1251235|title=Posibil caz de coronavirus \u00een Rom\u00e2nia. Reac\u021bia Ministerului S\u0103n\u0103t\u0103\u021bii: \"Este foarte pu\u021bin probabil\"|date=2020-01-27|access-date=2020-01-27|language=ro|website=digi24.ro|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127154230/https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/posibil-caz-de-coronavirus-in-romania-1251235|archive-date=2020-01-27|url-status=live}}</ref> but the first case would not be confirmed until 26 February.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hotnews.ro/stiri-sanatate-23687251-primul-caz-infectie-coronavirus-confirmat-oficial-romania.htm|title=Primul caz de infec\u021bie cu coronavirus, confirmat oficial \u00een Rom\u00e2nia: Un b\u0103rbat din Gorj ce a intrat \u00een contact cu italianul care a vizitat recent \u021bara noastr\u0103|website=HotNews.ro|author=Neagu, Alina|date=26 February 2020|access-date=3 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200226220952/https://www.hotnews.ro/stiri-sanatate-23687251-primul-caz-infectie-coronavirus-confirmat-oficial-romania.htm|archive-date=26 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mediafax.ro/coronavirus/detalii-despre-primul-roman-diagnosticat-cu-noul-coronavirus-are-20-de-ani-si-lucra-la-restaurantul-italianului-care-a-vizitat-recent-tara-noastra-18897127|title=Detalii despre primul rom\u00e2n diagnosticat cu noul coronavirus. Are 20 de ani \u0219i locuie\u0219te \u00een comuna Prigoria - UPDATE|website=Mediafax|author=Ficiu, Loredana|date=27 February 2020|access-date=11 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228181109/https://www.mediafax.ro/coronavirus/detalii-despre-primul-roman-diagnosticat-cu-noul-coronavirus-are-20-de-ani-si-lucra-la-restaurantul-italianului-care-a-vizitat-recent-tara-noastra-18897127|archive-date=28 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Ecuador reported a suspected case of coronavirus, a Chinese citizen who arrived from Hong Kong.,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ticotimes.net/2020/01/27/ecuador-reports-first-suspected-case-of-coronavirus|title=Ecuador reports first suspected case of coronavirus|website=The Tico Times Costa Rica|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127172129/https://ticotimes.net/2020/01/27/ecuador-reports-first-suspected-case-of-coronavirus|archive-date=2020-01-27|url-status=live}}</ref> but the first case would not be confirmed until 29 February.<ref name=ecuador.1>{{cite tweet|user=elcomerciocom|number=1233773816825946113|date=29 February 2020|title=Ministra de Salud confirma primer caso de #coronavirus en Ecuador.}}</ref> Fiji authorities are holding six Chinese travelers in quarantine in [[Nadi]] as a precaution after they failed to gain entry to Samoa due to Samoa's quarantine requirements that were implemented Friday. The quarantine requirements, imposed after an emergency Cabinet meeting, compel anyone who's been in China to \"self-quarantine\" in a country free from the coronavirus for 14 days.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.newshub.co.nz/home/world/2020/01/pacific-nations-on-alert-for-coronavirus-6-quarantined-in-fiji.html|title=Pacific nations on alert for coronavirus, 6 quarantined in Fiji|work=Newshub|access-date=2020-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127043627/https://www.newshub.co.nz/home/world/2020/01/pacific-nations-on-alert-for-coronavirus-6-quarantined-in-fiji.html|archive-date=2020-01-27|url-status=live}}</ref> In Poland, two children were admitted to the [[Krak\u00f3w]] hospital with the suspicion of coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://krakow.wyborcza.pl/krakow/7,44425,25638900,do-krakowskiego-szpita-trafilo-dwoje-dzieci-z-podejrzeniem-koronawirusa.html|language=pl|website=krakow.wyborcza.pl|access-date=2020-01-27|date=2020-01-27|title=Dwoje dzieci ze \u015al\u0105ska trafi\u0142o na dzieci\u0119cy oddzia\u0142 zaka\u017any krakowskiego szpitala im. \u017beromskiego. Wraz z rodzicami wraca\u0142y przez Pekin do kraju i zachorowa\u0142y|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127182321/https://krakow.wyborcza.pl/krakow/7,44425,25638900,do-krakowskiego-szpita-trafilo-dwoje-dzieci-z-podejrzeniem-koronawirusa.html|archive-date=2020-01-27|url-status=live}}</ref> In Mongolia a 14-year-old girl who was studying in China had fallen ill with a suspected case of pneumonia and laryngitis; she was pronounced dead on the same day. Health authorities have since taken a sample from the deceased girl to be analysed at the National Center for Communicable Diseases in [[Ulaanbaatar]].<ref name=\"auto3\">{{cite web|url=https://ikon.mn/n/1s32|title=\u0425\u044d\u043d\u0442\u0438\u0439 \u0430\u0439\u043c\u0433\u0438\u0439\u043d \u044d\u043c\u043d\u044d\u043b\u044d\u0433\u0442 \u043d\u0430\u0441 \u0431\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0430\u043d \u043e\u0445\u0438\u043d\u044b \u0446\u043e\u0433\u0446\u0441\u043e\u043e\u0441 \u0441\u043e\u0440\u044c\u0446 \u0430\u0432\u0447, \u0434\u044d\u044d\u0436\u0438\u0439\u0433 \u0425\u04e8\u0421\u04ae\u0422-\u0434 \u0438\u043b\u0433\u044d\u044d\u0441\u044d\u043d|last=iKon.mn|first=\u0413. \u04e8\u043b\u0437\u0438\u0439\u0445\u0443\u0442\u0430\u0433|date=2020-01-27|website=ikon.mn|access-date=2020-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127155037/https://ikon.mn/n/1s32|archive-date=2020-01-27|url-status=live}}</ref> Two Mongolian students returning from Taiwan to [[Chinggis Khaan International Airport]] have shown symptoms of high fever and rising temperature and were put into quarantine after landing in Mongolia.<ref name=\"auto3\"/> In Switzerland, two people were put under quarantine at the [[Triemli Hospital]] in Zurich; both had previously been to China.<ref>{{citation|url=https://www.srf.ch/news/international/corona-virus-auf-dem-vormarsch-verdachtsfaelle-in-der-schweiz-gemeldet|date=2020-01-27|language=de|access-date=2020-01-27|title=Verdachtsf\u00e4lle in der Schweiz gemeldet|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126220817/https://www.srf.ch/news/international/corona-virus-auf-dem-vormarsch-verdachtsfaelle-in-der-schweiz-gemeldet|archive-date=2020-01-26|url-status=live}}</ref> These cases later turned up negative.<ref>{{citation|url=https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/coronavirus_swiss-tighten-rules-to-help-stop-spread-of-china-virus/45518156|date=2020-01-27|language=en|access-date=2020-01-27|title=Two quarantined patients do not have coronavirus, confirms Zurich hospital|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127015652/https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/coronavirus_swiss-tighten-rules-to-help-stop-spread-of-china-virus/45518156|archive-date=2020-01-27|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn [[Germany]], the first specific, global case of coronavirus being transmitted by a person with no symptoms has been reported. The originally-infected individual is from [[Shanghai]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sciencenews.org/article/first-case-coronavirus-spread-person-no-symptoms-found-germany|title=The first case of coronavirus being spread by a person with no symptoms has been found|first=Tina Hesman|last=Saey|date=31 January 2020|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200203054720/https://www.sciencenews.org/article/first-case-coronavirus-spread-person-no-symptoms-found-germany|archive-date=3 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/study-reports-first-case-of-coronavirus-spread-by-asymptomatic-person/|title=Study Reports First Case of Coronavirus Spread By Asymptomatic Person|first=Andrew|last=Joseph,STAT|website=Scientific American|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200205163704/https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/study-reports-first-case-of-coronavirus-spread-by-asymptomatic-person/|archive-date=2020-02-05|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.statnews.com/2020/01/30/first-documented-case-of-coronavirus-spread-by-person-showing-no-symptoms/|title=First case of coronavirus spread by a person showing no symptoms|date=31 January 2020|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200205163743/https://www.statnews.com/2020/01/30/first-documented-case-of-coronavirus-spread-by-person-showing-no-symptoms/|archive-date=5 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Transmission of 2019-nCoV Infection from an Asymptomatic Contact in Germany|first1=Camilla|last1=Rothe|first2=Mirjam|last2=Schunk|first3=Peter|last3=Sothmann|first4=Gisela|last4=Bretzel|first5=Guenter|last5=Froeschl|first6=Claudia|last6=Wallrauch|first7=Thorbj\u00f6rn|last7=Zimmer|first8=Verena|last8=Thiel|first9=Christian|last9=Janke|first10=Wolfgang|last10=Guggemos|first11=Michael|last11=Seilmaier|first12=Christian|last12=Drosten |author-link12=Christian Drosten|first13=Patrick|last13=Vollmar|first14=Katrin|last14=Zwirglmaier|first15=Sabine|last15=Zange|first16=Roman|last16=W\u00f6lfel|first17=Michael|last17=Hoelscher|date=30 January 2020|journal=New England Journal of Medicine|volume=0|issue=10|pages=970\u2013971|doi=10.1056/NEJMc2001468|pmid= 32003551|pmc=7120970}}</ref>\n\nSouth Korean health officials met with Korean life science company representatives to speed the development of a test.<ref>Chad Terhune, Dan Levine, Hyunjoo Jin, and Jane Lanhee Lee. (18 March 2020). \"Special Report: How Korea trounced U.S. in race to test people for coronavirus\". [https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-testing-specialrep-idUSKBN2153BW Reuters website] Retrieved 21 March 2020.</ref>\n\nIn the US, there were surging increase of warnings from its intelligence agencies toward the end of January and into early February. The then-acting chief of staff Mick Mulvaney began convening regular meetings. In early briefings, however, officials said Trump was dismissive because he did not believe that the virus had spread widely throughout the United States.<ref name=\":11\" />\n\n===28 January===\nChina's Supreme People's Court through a message \u300a\u6cbb\u7406\u6709\u5173\u65b0\u578b\u80ba\u708e\u7684\u8c23\u8a00\u95ee\u9898\uff0c\u8fd9\u7bc7\u6587\u7ae0\u8bf4\u6e05\u695a\u4e86\uff01\u300bin its official WeChat account vindicated Dr. Li [[Li Wenliang|Wenliang]] and the other 7 doctors and said they should not have been punished as what they said was not entirely false.<ref name=\"web.archive.org\" /><ref name=\":3\">{{cite web|url=https://asia.nikkei.com/Spotlight/Caixin/Rebuked-coronavirus-whistleblower-vindicated-by-top-Chinese-court|title=Rebuked coronavirus whistleblower vindicated by top Chinese court|website=Nikkei Asian Review|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> The Court further stated that  \"based on the difference in cognitive level, different individuals may produce different degrees of false information about the same thing. We should permit the law's to have certain degree of tolerance towards individuals. For example, in the case of the 8 persons being punished by Wuhan Police for publishing \"7 SARS cases diagnosed in the Huanan Seafood Market\u201d, if we mechanically applying the law, since the new coronavirus infected pneumonia is not SARS, by saying SARS has emerged we can indeed determine that is fabrication of false information, and the information has caused chaos in the social order. In accordance with the law provided, administrative punishment and even criminal punishment can be justified for the act of fabricating and disseminating false information. However, the fact is the message is not entirely false. If society had at the time believed those 'rumours', and wore masks, used disinfectant and avoided going to the wildlife market as if there were a SARS outbreak, perhaps it will help us better control the coronavirus today\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.caixinglobal.com/2020-01-31/after-being-punished-by-local-police-coronavirus-whistleblower-vindicated-by-top-court-101509986.html|title=Whistleblower Li Wenliang: There Should Be More Than One Voice In A Healthy Society|website=www.caixinglobal.com|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200205002435/https://www.caixinglobal.com/2020-01-31/after-being-punished-by-local-police-coronavirus-whistleblower-vindicated-by-top-court-101509986.html|archive-date=2020-02-05|access-date=2020-02-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/ETgXN6HInzlC8cxzhDdU9g|publisher=[[Supreme People's Court]]|script-title=zh:\u6cbb\u7406\u6709\u5173\u65b0\u578b\u80ba\u708e\u7684\u8c23\u8a00\u95ee\u9898\uff0c\u8fd9\u7bc7\u6587\u7ae0\u8bf4\u6e05\u695a\u4e86!|trans-title=Regarding the issue of authorities handling the new novel coronavirus as rumours|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202004701/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/ETgXN6HInzlC8cxzhDdU9g|archive-date=2020-02-02|access-date=2020-02-08}}</ref>\n\n'''WHO''' Situation Report 8:<ref>{{Citation|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200128-sitrep-8-ncov-cleared.pdf?sfvrsn=8b671ce5_2|title=Novel Coronavirus(2019-nCoV) Situation Report - 8|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202195554/https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200128-sitrep-8-ncov-cleared.pdf?sfvrsn=8b671ce5_2|archive-date=2020-02-02|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThailand confirms six more cases, bringing the total infected there to 14. Thailand's health minister, [[Anutin Charnvirakul]], states that \"we are not able to stop the spread\" of coronavirus in the country.<ref name=\"auto11\">{{cite web|url=https://news.sky.com/story/thailand-not-able-to-stop-the-spread-of-new-coronavirus-11919860|title=Thailand 'not able to stop the spread' of new coronavirus|website=Sky News|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202160111/https://news.sky.com/story/thailand-not-able-to-stop-the-spread-of-new-coronavirus-11919860|archive-date=2020-02-02|url-status=live}}</ref> Singapore confirms two more cases, bringing the total infected in Singapore to seven. That was followed by a Hubei-related suspension from 29 January.<ref name=\"auto2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/wuhan-virus-7-confirmed-cases-in-singapore-no-entry-or-transit-for-new-visitors-with-hubei|title=Wuhan virus: 2 new confirmed cases in Singapore, bringing total to 7; no entry or transit for new visitors from Hubei|website=The Straits Times|accessdate=28 January 2020|date=28 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128094942/https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/wuhan-virus-7-confirmed-cases-in-singapore-no-entry-or-transit-for-new-visitors-with-hubei|archive-date=28 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Japan confirms 3 additional cases, bringing the total infected in Japan to seven, including a man who had never visited Wuhan. He was working as a tour bus driver and had driven a group from Wuhan earlier in January.<ref name=\"auto8\">{{cite web|url=https://english.kyodonews.net/news/2020/01/e8f47252a245-urgent-japan-sees-1st-coronavirus-case-not-linked-to-recent-travel-to-china.html|title=Japan sees 1st coronavirus case not linked to recent travel to China|date=28 January 2020|via=Kyodo News|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129162636/https://english.kyodonews.net/news/2020/01/e8f47252a245-urgent-japan-sees-1st-coronavirus-case-not-linked-to-recent-travel-to-china.html|archive-date=29 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"auto10\">{{cite news|url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2020/01/28/national/japan-charter-flights-evacuate-japanese-virus-wuhan-china/#.XjAFCLdlB-E|title=Japan reports new coronavirus cases as it moves to evacuate nationals from Wuhan|newspaper=The Japan Times Online|date=28 January 2020|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128134009/https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2020/01/28/national/japan-charter-flights-evacuate-japanese-virus-wuhan-china/#.XjAFCLdlB-E|archive-date=28 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Germany's first confirmed case, reported the previous day, had occurred in a German citizen who had not travelled to China. However, he had close contact with a visiting Chinese colleague who reported starting to feel ill during her return flight to Shanghai and she was diagnosed with coronavirus infection after arriving in China. Germany confirmed 3 new cases, all of whom were coworkers of the first confirmed patient.<ref name=\"auto6\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sueddeutsche.de/gesundheit/coronavirus-drei-weitere-infizierte-in-bayern-1.4776016|title=Drei weitere Infizierte in Bayern|last=Zeitung|first=S\u00fcddeutsche|website=S\u00fcddeutsche.de|language=de|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref> France confirmed its fourth case, an elderly Chinese tourist who is in critical condition.<ref name=\"auto5\">{{cite web|url=https://www.france24.com/fr/20200128-nouveau-coronavirus-quatri%C3%A8me-cas-en-france-le-patient-en-r%C3%A9animation|title=Quatri\u00e8me cas en France, le patient en r\u00e9animation|last=|first=|date=28 January 2020|website=Franceinfo|language=fr|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref>\n\nThe Brazilian [[Ministry of Health (Brazil)|Ministry of Health]] reports three suspected cases ongoing in three locations: [[Belo Horizonte]] (MG), [[Curitiba]] (PR) and [[S\u00e3o Leopoldo]] (RS).<ref name=\"auto7\">{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/ciencia-e-saude/noticia/2020/01/28/brasil-tem-2-novos-casos-suspeitos-de-coronavirus-em-porto-alegre-e-curitiba-ministerio.ghtml|title=Brasil tem 2 novos casos suspeitos de coronav\u00edrus em S\u00e3o Leopoldo e em Curitiba, diz Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade|website=G1|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131042625/https://g1.globo.com/ciencia-e-saude/noticia/2020/01/28/brasil-tem-2-novos-casos-suspeitos-de-coronavirus-em-porto-alegre-e-curitiba-ministerio.ghtml|archive-date=2020-01-31|url-status=live}}</ref> Canada reports a new presumptive case in [[British Columbia]], a man in his 40s who had recently travelled to Wuhan.<ref name=\"auto12\">{{cite web|url=https://globalnews.ca/news/6473048/bc-coronavirus-update-tuesday-jan-28/|title=First presumptive case of coronavirus confirmed in B.C.|website=Global News|language=en|access-date=2020-01-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128183227/https://globalnews.ca/news/6473048/bc-coronavirus-update-tuesday-jan-28/|archive-date=2020-01-28|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nA UK-Chinese medical research paper reports a statistical model finding that \"estimates suggest the actual number of infected cases could be much higher than the reported, with estimated 26,701 cases (as of 28th January 2020).\"<ref>{{cite journal|url=https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/2020.01.27.922443v1|title=Breaking down of the healthcare system: Mathematical modelling for controlling the novel coronavirus (2019-nCoV) outbreak in Wuhan, China|first1=Wai-kit|last1=Ming|first2=Jian|last2=Huang|first3=Casper J. P.|last3=Zhang|date=28 January 2020|journal=bioRxiv|pages=2020.01.27.922443|via=www.biorxiv.org|doi=10.1101/2020.01.27.922443|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201160242/https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/2020.01.27.922443v1|archive-date=1 February 2020|url-status=live|doi-access=free}}</ref>\n\nScientists from The Peter Doherty Institute for Infection and Immunity (Doherty Institute) in Melbourne reported that they had successfully grown 2019-nCoV from a patient sample.<ref name=\"auto9\">{{cite web|url=https://www.doherty.edu.au/news-events/news/coronavirus|title=Doherty Institute scientists first to grow and share Wuhan coronavirus|last=|first=|date=|website=www.doherty.edu.au|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128203302/https://www.doherty.edu.au/news-events/news/coronavirus|archive-date=2020-01-28|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref>\n\n[[Xiangyang]] became quarantined starting 00:00;<ref name=\":101\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thepaper.cn/newsDetail_forward_5671283|title=\u8944\u9633\u706b\u8f66\u7ad9\u5173\u95ed\uff0c\u6e56\u5317\u7701\u6700\u540e\u4e00\u4e2a\u5730\u7ea7\u5e02\"\u5c01\u57ce\"_\u5a92\u4f53_\u6f8e\u6e43\u65b0\u95fb-The Paper|website=www.thepaper.cn|access-date=2020-02-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202170024/https://www.thepaper.cn/newsDetail_forward_5671283|archive-date=2020-02-02|url-status=live}}</ref> the entire Hubei province thus became quarantined save for [[Shennongjia Forestry District]].\n\nA senior medical adviser at the Department of Veterans Affairs, Dr. Carter Mecher, wrote on the night of Jan. 28, in an email to a group of public health experts scattered around the government and universities. \u201cThe projected size of the outbreak already seems hard to believe.\"<ref>{{Cite news|last=Lipton|first=Eric|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/11/us/politics/coronavirus-trump-response.html|title=He Could Have Seen What Was Coming: Behind Trump\u2019s Failure on the Virus|date=2020-04-11|website=[[The New York Times]]|access-date=2020-04-13|last2=Sanger|first2=David E.|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331|last3=Haberman|first3=Maggie|last4=Shear|first4=Michael D.|last5=Mazzetti|first5=Mark|last6=Barnes|first6=Julian E.}}</ref>\n\n===29 January===\n'''WHO''' Situation Report 9:<ref name=\"auto13\">{{Citation|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200129-sitrep-9-ncov-v2.pdf?sfvrsn=e2c8915_2|title=Novel Coronavirus(2019-nCoV) Situation Report - 9|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206035856/https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200129-sitrep-9-ncov-v2.pdf?sfvrsn=e2c8915_2|archive-date=2020-02-06|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[Tibet Autonomous Region|Tibet]] reported its first suspected case identified on the previous day<ref name=\"sina_tibet\">{{cite web|url=https://news.sina.com.cn/c/2020-01-29/doc-iihnzhha5188508.shtml|title=\u897f\u85cf\u65b0\u589e\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd