 for 14 days.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.newshub.co.nz/home/world/2020/01/pacific-nations-on-alert-for-coronavirus-6-quarantined-in-fiji.html|title=Pacific nations on alert for coronavirus, 6 quarantined in Fiji|work=Newshub|access-date=2020-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127043627/https://www.newshub.co.nz/home/world/2020/01/pacific-nations-on-alert-for-coronavirus-6-quarantined-in-fiji.html|archive-date=2020-01-27|url-status=live}}</ref> In Poland, two children were admitted to the [[Krak\u00f3w]] hospital with the suspicion of coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://krakow.wyborcza.pl/krakow/7,44425,25638900,do-krakowskiego-szpita-trafilo-dwoje-dzieci-z-podejrzeniem-koronawirusa.html|language=pl|website=krakow.wyborcza.pl|access-date=2020-01-27|date=2020-01-27|title=Dwoje dzieci ze \u015al\u0105ska trafi\u0142o na dzieci\u0119cy oddzia\u0142 zaka\u017any krakowskiego szpitala im. \u017beromskiego. Wraz z rodzicami wraca\u0142y przez Pekin do kraju i zachorowa\u0142y|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127182321/https://krakow.wyborcza.pl/krakow/7,44425,25638900,do-krakowskiego-szpita-trafilo-dwoje-dzieci-z-podejrzeniem-koronawirusa.html|archive-date=2020-01-27|url-status=live}}</ref> In Mongolia a 14-year-old girl who was studying in China had fallen ill with a suspected case of pneumonia and laryngitis; she was pronounced dead on the same day. Health authorities have since taken a sample from the deceased girl to be analysed at the National Center for Communicable Diseases in [[Ulaanbaatar]].<ref name=\"auto3\">{{cite web|url=https://ikon.mn/n/1s32|title=\u0425\u044d\u043d\u0442\u0438\u0439 \u0430\u0439\u043c\u0433\u0438\u0439\u043d \u044d\u043c\u043d\u044d\u043b\u044d\u0433\u0442 \u043d\u0430\u0441 \u0431\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0430\u043d \u043e\u0445\u0438\u043d\u044b \u0446\u043e\u0433\u0446\u0441\u043e\u043e\u0441 \u0441\u043e\u0440\u044c\u0446 \u0430\u0432\u0447, \u0434\u044d\u044d\u0436\u0438\u0439\u0433 \u0425\u04e8\u0421\u04ae\u0422-\u0434 \u0438\u043b\u0433\u044d\u044d\u0441\u044d\u043d|last=iKon.mn|first=\u0413. \u04e8\u043b\u0437\u0438\u0439\u0445\u0443\u0442\u0430\u0433|date=2020-01-27|website=ikon.mn|access-date=2020-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127155037/https://ikon.mn/n/1s32|archive-date=2020-01-27|url-status=live}}</ref> Two Mongolian students returning from Taiwan to [[Chinggis Khaan International Airport]] have shown symptoms of high fever and rising temperature and were put into quarantine after landing in Mongolia.<ref name=\"auto3\"/> In Switzerland, two people were put under quarantine at the [[Triemli Hospital]] in Zurich; both had previously been to China.<ref>{{citation|url=https://www.srf.ch/news/international/corona-virus-auf-dem-vormarsch-verdachtsfaelle-in-der-schweiz-gemeldet|date=2020-01-27|language=de|access-date=2020-01-27|title=Verdachtsf\u00e4lle in der Schweiz gemeldet|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126220817/https://www.srf.ch/news/international/corona-virus-auf-dem-vormarsch-verdachtsfaelle-in-der-schweiz-gemeldet|archive-date=2020-01-26|url-status=live}}</ref> These cases later turned up negative.<ref>{{citation|url=https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/coronavirus_swiss-tighten-rules-to-help-stop-spread-of-china-virus/45518156|date=2020-01-27|language=en|access-date=2020-01-27|title=Two quarantined patients do not have coronavirus, confirms Zurich hospital|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127015652/https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/coronavirus_swiss-tighten-rules-to-help-stop-spread-of-china-virus/45518156|archive-date=2020-01-27|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn [[Germany]], the first specific, global case of coronavirus being transmitted by a person with no symptoms has been reported. The originally-infected individual is from [[Shanghai]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sciencenews.org/article/first-case-coronavirus-spread-person-no-symptoms-found-germany|title=The first case of coronavirus being spread by a person with no symptoms has been found|first=Tina Hesman|last=Saey|date=31 January 2020|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200203054720/https://www.sciencenews.org/article/first-case-coronavirus-spread-person-no-symptoms-found-germany|archive-date=3 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/study-reports-first-case-of-coronavirus-spread-by-asymptomatic-person/|title=Study Reports First Case of Coronavirus Spread By Asymptomatic Person|first=Andrew|last=Joseph,STAT|website=Scientific American|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200205163704/https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/study-reports-first-case-of-coronavirus-spread-by-asymptomatic-person/|archive-date=2020-02-05|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.statnews.com/2020/01/30/first-documented-case-of-coronavirus-spread-by-person-showing-no-symptoms/|title=First case of coronavirus spread by a person showing no symptoms|date=31 January 2020|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200205163743/https://www.statnews.com/2020/01/30/first-documented-case-of-coronavirus-spread-by-person-showing-no-symptoms/|archive-date=5 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Transmission of 2019-nCoV Infection from an Asymptomatic Contact in Germany|first1=Camilla|last1=Rothe|first2=Mirjam|last2=Schunk|first3=Peter|last3=Sothmann|first4=Gisela|last4=Bretzel|first5=Guenter|last5=Froeschl|first6=Claudia|last6=Wallrauch|first7=Thorbj\u00f6rn|last7=Zimmer|first8=Verena|last8=Thiel|first9=Christian|last9=Janke|first10=Wolfgang|last10=Guggemos|first11=Michael|last11=Seilmaier|first12=Christian|last12=Drosten |author-link12=Christian Drosten|first13=Patrick|last13=Vollmar|first14=Katrin|last14=Zwirglmaier|first15=Sabine|last15=Zange|first16=Roman|last16=W\u00f6lfel|first17=Michael|last17=Hoelscher|date=30 January 2020|journal=New England Journal of Medicine|volume=0|issue=10|pages=970\u2013971|doi=10.1056/NEJMc2001468|pmid= 32003551|pmc=7120970}}</ref>\n\nSouth Korean health officials met with Korean life science company representatives to speed the development of a test.<ref>Chad Terhune, Dan Levine, Hyunjoo Jin, and Jane Lanhee Lee. (18 March 2020). \"Special Report: How Korea trounced U.S. in race to test people for coronavirus\". [https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-testing-specialrep-idUSKBN2153BW Reuters website] Retrieved 21 March 2020.</ref>\n\nIn the US, there were surging increase of warnings from its intelligence agencies toward the end of January and into early February. The then-acting chief of staff Mick Mulvaney began convening regular meetings. In early briefings, however, officials said Trump was dismissive because he did not believe that the virus had spread widely throughout the United States.<ref name=\":11\" />\n\n===28 January===\nChina's Supreme People's Court through a message \u300a\u6cbb\u7406\u6709\u5173\u65b0\u578b\u80ba\u708e\u7684\u8c23\u8a00\u95ee\u9898\uff0c\u8fd9\u7bc7\u6587\u7ae0\u8bf4\u6e05\u695a\u4e86\uff01\u300bin its official WeChat account vindicated Dr. Li [[Li Wenliang|Wenliang]] and the other 7 doctors and said they should not have been punished as what they said was not entirely false.<ref name=\"web.archive.org\" /><ref name=\":3\">{{cite web|url=https://asia.nikkei.com/Spotlight/Caixin/Rebuked-coronavirus-whistleblower-vindicated-by-top-Chinese-court|title=Rebuked coronavirus whistleblower vindicated by top Chinese court|website=Nikkei Asian Review|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> The Court further stated that  \"based on the difference in cognitive level, different individuals may produce different degrees of false information about the same thing. We should permit the law's to have certain degree of tolerance towards individuals. For example, in the case of the 8 persons being punished by Wuhan Police for publishing \"7 SARS cases diagnosed in the Huanan Seafood Market\u201d, if we mechanically applying the law, since the new coronavirus infected pneumonia is not SARS, by saying SARS has emerged we can indeed determine that is fabrication of false information, and the information has caused chaos in the social order. In accordance with the law provided, administrative punishment and even criminal punishment can be justified for the act of fabricating and disseminating false information. However, the fact is the message is not entirely false. If society had at the time believed those 'rumours', and wore masks, used disinfectant and avoided going to the wildlife market as if there were a SARS outbreak, perhaps it will help us better control the coronavirus today\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.caixinglobal.com/2020-01-31/after-being-punished-by-local-police-coronavirus-whistleblower-vindicated-by-top-court-101509986.html|title=Whistleblower Li Wenliang: There Should Be More Than One Voice In A Healthy Society|website=www.caixinglobal.com|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200205002435/https://www.caixinglobal.com/2020-01-31/after-being-punished-by-local-police-coronavirus-whistleblower-vindicated-by-top-court-101509986.html|archive-date=2020-02-05|access-date=2020-02-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/ETgXN6HInzlC8cxzhDdU9g|publisher=[[Supreme People's Court]]|script-title=zh:\u6cbb\u7406\u6709\u5173\u65b0\u578b\u80ba\u708e\u7684\u8c23\u8a00\u95ee\u9898\uff0c\u8fd9\u7bc7\u6587\u7ae0\u8bf4\u6e05\u695a\u4e86!|trans-title=Regarding the issue of authorities handling the new novel coronavirus as rumours|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202004701/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/ETgXN6HInzlC8cxzhDdU9g|archive-date=2020-02-02|access-date=2020-02-08}}</ref>\n\n'''WHO''' Situation Report 8:<ref>{{Citation|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200128-sitrep-8-ncov-cleared.pdf?sfvrsn=8b671ce5_2|title=Novel Coronavirus(2019-nCoV) Situation Report - 8|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202195554/https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200128-sitrep-8-ncov-cleared.pdf?sfvrsn=8b671ce5_2|archive-date=2020-02-02|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThailand confirms six more cases, bringing the total infected there to 14. Thailand's health minister, [[Anutin Charnvirakul]], states that \"we are not able to stop the spread\" of coronavirus in the country.<ref name=\"auto11\">{{cite web|url=https://news.sky.com/story/thailand-not-able-to-stop-the-spread-of-new-coronavirus-11919860|title=Thailand 'not able to stop the spread' of new coronavirus|website=Sky News|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202160111/https://news.sky.com/story/thailand-not-able-to-stop-the-spread-of-new-coronavirus-11919860|archive-date=2020-02-02|url-status=live}}</ref> Singapore confirms two more cases, bringing the total infected in Singapore to seven. That was followed by a Hubei-related suspension from 29 January.<ref name=\"auto2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/wuhan-virus-7-confirmed-cases-in-singapore-no-entry-or-transit-for-new-visitors-with-hubei|title=Wuhan virus: 2 new confirmed cases in Singapore, bringing total to 7; no entry or transit for new visitors from Hubei|website=The Straits Times|accessdate=28 January 2020|date=28 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128094942/https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/wuhan-virus-7-confirmed-cases-in-singapore-no-entry-or-transit-for-new-visitors-with-hubei|archive-date=28 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Japan confirms 3 additional cases, bringing the total infected in Japan to seven, including a man who had never visited Wuhan. He was working as a tour bus driver and had driven a group from Wuhan earlier in January.<ref name=\"auto8\">{{cite web|url=https://english.kyodonews.net/news/2020/01/e8f47252a245-urgent-japan-sees-1st-coronavirus-case-not-linked-to-recent-travel-to-china.html|title=Japan sees 1st coronavirus case not linked to recent travel to China|date=28 January 2020|via=Kyodo News|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129162636/https://english.kyodonews.net/news/2020/01/e8f47252a245-urgent-japan-sees-1st-coronavirus-case-not-linked-to-recent-travel-to-china.html|archive-date=29 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"auto10\">{{cite news|url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2020/01/28/national/japan-charter-flights-evacuate-japanese-virus-wuhan-china/#.XjAFCLdlB-E|title=Japan reports new coronavirus cases as it moves to evacuate nationals from Wuhan|newspaper=The Japan Times Online|date=28 January 2020|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128134009/https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2020/01/28/national/japan-charter-flights-evacuate-japanese-virus-wuhan-china/#.XjAFCLdlB-E|archive-date=28 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Germany's first confirmed case, reported the previous day, had occurred in a German citizen who had not travelled to China. However, he had close contact with a visiting Chinese colleague who reported starting to feel ill during her return flight to Shanghai and she was diagnosed with coronavirus infection after arriving in China. Germany confirmed 3 new cases, all of whom were coworkers of the first confirmed patient.<ref name=\"auto6\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sueddeutsche.de/gesundheit/coronavirus-drei-weitere-infizierte-in-bayern-1.4776016|title=Drei weitere Infizierte in Bayern|last=Zeitung|first=S\u00fcddeutsche|website=S\u00fcddeutsche.de|language=de|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref> France confirmed its fourth case, an elderly Chinese tourist who is in critical condition.<ref name=\"auto5\">{{cite web|url=https://www.france24.com/fr/20200128-nouveau-coronavirus-quatri%C3%A8me-cas-en-france-le-patient-en-r%C3%A9animation|title=Quatri\u00e8me cas en France, le patient en r\u00e9animation|last=|first=|date=28 January 2020|website=Franceinfo|language=fr|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref>\n\nThe Brazilian [[Ministry of Health (Brazil)|Ministry of Health]] reports three suspected cases ongoing in three locations: [[Belo Horizonte]] (MG), [[Curitiba]] (PR) and [[S\u00e3o Leopoldo]] (RS).<ref name=\"auto7\">{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/ciencia-e-saude/noticia/2020/01/28/brasil-tem-2-novos-casos-suspeitos-de-coronavirus-em-porto-alegre-e-curitiba-ministerio.ghtml|title=Brasil tem 2 novos casos suspeitos de coronav\u00edrus em S\u00e3o Leopoldo e em Curitiba, diz Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade|website=G1|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131042625/https://g1.globo.com/ciencia-e-saude/noticia/2020/01/28/brasil-tem-2-novos-casos-suspeitos-de-coronavirus-em-porto-alegre-e-curitiba-ministerio.ghtml|archive-date=2020-01-31|url-status=live}}</ref> Canada reports a new presumptive case in [[British Columbia]], a man in his 40s who had recently travelled to Wuhan.<ref name=\"auto12\">{{cite web|url=https://globalnews.ca/news/6473048/bc-coronavirus-update-tuesday-jan-28/|title=First presumptive case of coronavirus confirmed in B.C.|website=Global News|language=en|access-date=2020-01-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128183227/https://globalnews.ca/news/6473048/bc-coronavirus-update-tuesday-jan-28/|archive-date=2020-01-28|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nA UK-Chinese medical research paper reports a statistical model finding that \"estimates suggest the actual number of infected cases could be much higher than the reported, with estimated 26,701 cases (as of 28th January 2020).\"<ref>{{cite journal|url=https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/2020.01.27.922443v1|title=Breaking down of the healthcare system: Mathematical modelling for controlling the novel coronavirus (2019-nCoV) outbreak in Wuhan, China|first1=Wai-kit|last1=Ming|first2=Jian|last2=Huang|first3=Casper J. P.|last3=Zhang|date=28 January 2020|journal=bioRxiv|pages=2020.01.27.922443|via=www.biorxiv.org|doi=10.1101/2020.01.27.922443|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201160242/https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/2020.01.27.922443v1|archive-date=1 February 2020|url-status=live|doi-access=free}}</ref>\n\nScientists from The Peter Doherty Institute for Infection and Immunity (Doherty Institute) in Melbourne reported that they had successfully grown 2019-nCoV from a patient sample.<ref name=\"auto9\">{{cite web|url=https://www.doherty.edu.au/news-events/news/coronavirus|title=Doherty Institute scientists first to grow and share Wuhan coronavirus|last=|first=|date=|website=www.doherty.edu.au|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128203302/https://www.doherty.edu.au/news-events/news/coronavirus|archive-date=2020-01-28|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref>\n\n[[Xiangyang]] became quarantined starting 00:00;<ref name=\":101\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thepaper.cn/newsDetail_forward_5671283|title=\u8944\u9633\u706b\u8f66\u7ad9\u5173\u95ed\uff0c\u6e56\u5317\u7701\u6700\u540e\u4e00\u4e2a\u5730\u7ea7\u5e02\"\u5c01\u57ce\"_\u5a92\u4f53_\u6f8e\u6e43\u65b0\u95fb-The Paper|website=www.thepaper.cn|access-date=2020-02-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202170024/https://www.thepaper.cn/newsDetail_forward_5671283|archive-date=2020-02-02|url-status=live}}</ref> the entire Hubei province thus became quarantined save for [[Shennongjia Forestry District]].\n\nA senior medical adviser at the Department of Veterans Affairs, Dr. Carter Mecher, wrote on the night of Jan. 28, in an email to a group of public health experts scattered around the government and universities. \u201cThe projected size of the outbreak already seems hard to believe.\"<ref>{{Cite news|last=Lipton|first=Eric|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/11/us/politics/coronavirus-trump-response.html|title=He Could Have Seen What Was Coming: Behind Trump\u2019s Failure on the Virus|date=2020-04-11|website=[[The New York Times]]|access-date=2020-04-13|last2=Sanger|first2=David E.|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331|last3=Haberman|first3=Maggie|last4=Shear|first4=Michael D.|last5=Mazzetti|first5=Mark|last6=Barnes|first6=Julian E.}}</ref>\n\n===29 January===\n'''WHO''' Situation Report 9:<ref name=\"auto13\">{{Citation|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200129-sitrep-9-ncov-v2.pdf?sfvrsn=e2c8915_2|title=Novel Coronavirus(2019-nCoV) Situation Report - 9|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206035856/https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200129-sitrep-9-ncov-v2.pdf?sfvrsn=e2c8915_2|archive-date=2020-02-06|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[Tibet Autonomous Region|Tibet]] reported its first suspected case identified on the previous day<ref name=\"sina_tibet\">{{cite web|url=https://news.sina.com.cn/c/2020-01-29/doc-iihnzhha5188508.shtml|title=\u897f\u85cf\u65b0\u589e\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u80ba\u708e1\u4f8b\u7591\u4f3c\u75c5\u4f8b|last=\u4eba\u6c11\u65e5\u62a5|date=2020-01-29|website=news.sina.com.cn|access-date=2020-01-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129034117/https://news.sina.com.cn/c/2020-01-29/doc-iihnzhha5188508.shtml|archive-date=2020-01-29|url-status=live|language=zh-cn}}</ref> and declared a level 1 health emergency in the evening, the last mainland provincial division to do so.<ref name=\"tibet_emer\">{{cite web |title=\u897f\u85cf\u542f\u52a8\u91cd\u5927\u7a81\u53d1\u516c\u5171\u536b\u751f\u4e8b\u4ef6I\u7ea7\u54cd\u5e94_\u6eda\u52a8\u65b0\u95fb_\u4e2d\u56fd\u653f\u5e9c\u7f51 |url=http://www.gov.cn/xinwen/2020-01/29/content_5472988.htm |website=www.gov.cn |accessdate=29 January 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200412170458/http://www.gov.cn/xinwen/2020-01/29/content_5472988.htm |archivedate=12 April 2020 |language=zh |date=29 January 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> Suspected cases have now been reported in all 31 mainland provincial divisions.\n\nCompanies in Hubei are required not to resume services before 13 February, and schools in Hubei are to postpone the reopening of schools.<ref name=\":14\">{{cite web|url=http://cnhubei.com/content/2020-01/29/content_12659024.html|title=\u6e56\u5317\u7701\u5404\u7c7b\u4f01\u4e1a\u590d\u5de5\u65f6\u95f4\u4e0d\u65e9\u4e8e2\u670813\u65e524\u65f6|language=zh|date=2020-01-29|website=cnhubei.com|accessdate=2020-01-29}}</ref>\n\nThe [[United Arab Emirates|UAE]] confirms its first case.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://gulfnews.com/uae/health/coronavirus-first-case-confirmed-in-uae-1.1580273983681|title=Coronavirus: First case confirmed in UAE|website=gulfnews.com|accessdate=2020-01-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129051659/https://gulfnews.com/uae/health/coronavirus-first-case-confirmed-in-uae-1.1580273983681|archive-date=2020-01-29|url-status=live}}</ref> Shortly afterwards, an [[Emirates (airline)|Emirates]]' news agency confirmed four people from a Chinese family to be infected.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://gulfnews.com/uae/health/coronavirus-in-uae-four-of-a-family-infected-1.1580273983681|title=Coronavirus in UAE: Four of a family infected|website=gulfnews.com|accessdate=2020-01-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129111625/https://gulfnews.com/uae/health/coronavirus-in-uae-four-of-a-family-infected-1.1580273983681|archive-date=2020-01-29|url-status=live}}</ref> Finland reports its first case of the virus in [[Lapland (Finland)|Lapland]], found in a Chinese tourist who left Wuhan before Wuhan was locked down.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://yle.fi/uutiset/osasto/news/finlands_first_coronavirus_case_confirmed_in_lapland/11182855|title=Finland's first coronavirus case confirmed in Lapland|date=2020-01-29|publisher=YLE|location=Finland|accessdate=2020-01-30}}</ref> Singapore confirms three more cases of the virus, bringing the total infected to 10.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/wuhan-virus-singapore-new-confirmed-cases-coronavirus-12364556|title=Singapore confirms 3 new cases of Wuhan virus; total of 10 infected|accessdate=2020-01-29|website=CNA|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129112711/https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/wuhan-virus-singapore-new-confirmed-cases-coronavirus-12364556|archive-date=2020-01-29|url-status=live}}</ref> Malaysia confirms three additional cases, bringing its total to seven.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nst.com.my/news/nation/2020/01/560544/three-more-positive-coronavirus-cases-malaysia-bringing-total-7|title=Three more positive coronavirus cases in Malaysia, bringing total to 7|publisher=New Straits Times|date=2020-01-29|url-status=live|accessdate=2020-01-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129012136/https://www.nst.com.my/news/nation/2020/01/560544/three-more-positive-coronavirus-cases-malaysia-bringing-total-7|archive-date=2020-01-29}}</ref> Japan reports four additional cases, including a tour bus guide that was on the same bus as one of the cases confirmed on 28 January<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www3.nhk.or.jp/news/html/20200129/k10012264621000.html|title=\u30d0\u30b9\u3067\u30ac\u30a4\u30c9 \u5927\u962a\u306e\u5973\u6027 \u30a6\u30a4\u30eb\u30b9\u306b\u611f\u67d3 \u5948\u826f\u306e\u904b\u8ee2\u624b\u3068\u540c\u4e57|last=\u65e5\u672c\u653e\u9001\u5354\u4f1a|language=Japanese|location=Japan|website=[[NHK]]|accessdate=2020-01-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129123513/https://www3.nhk.or.jp/news/html/20200129/k10012264621000.html|archive-date=29 January 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> and three evacuated from Wuhan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www3.nhk.or.jp/news/html/20200130/k10012264981000.html|title=\u65b0\u578b\u80ba\u708e 29\u65e5\u5e30\u56fd\u306e\uff13\u4eba\u611f\u67d3\u78ba\u8a8d \u3046\u30612\u4eba\u306f\u767a\u71b1\u306a\u3069\u75c7\u72b6\u306a\u3057|website=[[NHK]]|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130235311/https://www3.nhk.or.jp/news/html/20200130/k10012264981000.html|archive-date=30 January 2020|url-status=dead|language=jp}}</ref> France confirmed a fifth case, the daughter of the patient in the fourth case.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bfmtv.com/sante/coronavirus-en-france-un-cinquieme-cas-confirme-la-fille-du-touriste-chinois-hospitalise-a-paris-1849280.html|title=Coronavirus en France: un cinqui\u00e8me cas confirm\u00e9, la fille du touriste chinois hospitalis\u00e9 \u00e0 Paris|language=French|trans-title=Coronavirus in France: A fifth case confirmed, the daughter of a Chinese tourist hospitalised in Paris|work=BFM TV|date=29 January 2020|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130195933/https://www.bfmtv.com/sante/coronavirus-en-france-un-cinquieme-cas-confirme-la-fille-du-touriste-chinois-hospitalise-a-paris-1849280.html|archive-date=30 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nTwo Chinese nationals were placed in isolation wards in [[Armenia]] amid the first suspected case of coronavirus in the country. The Chinese nationals were tourists travelling to Armenia from neighbouring [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]]. Liana Torosyan, the head of the Department of Infectious Diseases, advised that samples will be sent to European labs, as Armenia does not have the capacity to test for the novel coronavirus.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://armenpress.am/eng/news/1002962.html|title=Two Chinese nationals placed in isolation wards in Armenia amid first suspected case of coronavirus|date=29 January 2020|website=Armenpress.am|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201155551/https://armenpress.am/eng/news/1002962.html|archive-date=1 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Brazil reports a total of 9 suspected cases in six states of the country.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/01/29/brasil-tem-nove-casos-suspeitos-de-coronavirus-e-33-notificacoes.ghtml|title=Brasil tem 9 casos suspeitos de coronav\u00edrus em 6 estados|publisher=O Globo|location=Brazil|language=Portuguese|website=G1|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129210423/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/01/29/brasil-tem-nove-casos-suspeitos-de-coronavirus-e-33-notificacoes.ghtml|archive-date=2020-01-29|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAir Canada is halting all direct flights to China following the federal government's advisory to avoid non-essential travel to the mainland due to the coronavirus epidemic. The suspension is effective Thursday and slated to last until February 29.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vancouverisland.ctvnews.ca/air-canada-suspends-all-direct-flights-to-china-as-coronavirus-spreads-1.4789002|title=Air Canada suspends all direct flights to China as coronavirus spreads|date=29 January 2020|website=Vancouver Island|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201014048/https://vancouverisland.ctvnews.ca/air-canada-suspends-all-direct-flights-to-china-as-coronavirus-spreads-1.4789002|archive-date=1 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nTrump administration trade advisor [[Peter Navarro]] issued a memo warning that coronavirus could \"evolv[e] into a full-blown pandemic, imperiling the lives of millions of Americans\" and that the \"risk of a worst-case pandemic scenario should not be overlooked\". A critic of the Chinese government before the pandemic, Navarro argued for restrictions on travel from China.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Haberman |first1=Maggie |title=Trade Adviser Warned White House in January of Risks of a Pandemic |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/06/us/politics/navarro-warning-trump-coronavirus.html?action=click&module=Spotlight&pgtype=Homepage |accessdate=7 April 2020 |website=[[The New York Times]] |date=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe Wuhan police clarified that Dr. Li Wenliang was not arrested nor fined, but was warned as he had spread that \"there had been 7 confirmed cases of SARS\", which was not true.<ref name=\"weibo1\" />\n\n===30 January===\n'''WHO''' Situation Report 10:<ref>{{Citation|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200130-sitrep-10-ncov.pdf?sfvrsn=d0b2e480_2|title=Novel Coronavirus(2019-nCoV) Situation Report - 10|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131005409/https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200130-sitrep-10-ncov.pdf|archive-date=2020-01-31|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nWHO declared the virus was a [[Public Health Emergency of International Concern]] and advised \"all countries should be prepared for containment, including active surveillance, early detection, isolation and case management, contact tracing and prevention of onward spread of 2019-nCoV infection, and to share full data with WHO.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.who.int/news-room/detail/30-01-2020-statement-on-the-second-meeting-of-the-international-health-regulations-(2005)-emergency-committee-regarding-the-outbreak-of-novel-coronavirus-(2019-ncov)|title=Statement on the second meeting of the International Health Regulations (2005) Emergency Committee regarding the outbreak of novel coronavirus (2019-nCoV)|website=www.who.int|language=en|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n\nTibet confirms its first case, which was previously suspected.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wjw.xizang.gov.cn/xwzx/wsjkdt/202001/t20200130_131185.html|title=\u897f\u85cf\u81ea\u6cbb\u533a\u786e\u8bca\u9996\u4f8b\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u611f\u67d3\u7684\u80ba\u708e\u75c5\u4f8b_\u897f\u85cf\u81ea\u6cbb\u533a\u536b\u751f\u5065\u5eb7\u59d4\u5458\u4f1a|website=wjw.xizang.gov.cn|access-date=2020-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130000144/http://wjw.xizang.gov.cn/xwzx/wsjkdt/202001/t20200130_131185.html|archive-date=2020-01-30|url-status=live|language=zh-cn}}</ref> Cases have now been confirmed in all 31 provincial divisions of mainland China.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-china-51305526|title=Coronavirus: Death toll rises as virus spreads to every Chinese region|work=BBC News|date=30 January 2020|access-date=2020-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130030316/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-china-51305526|archive-date=2020-01-30|url-status=live}}</ref> India confirms its first case of coronavirus in a student who had returned from [[Wuhan University]] to the Indian state of [[Kerala]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Kerala reports first confirmed coronavirus case in India|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/kerala-reports-first-confirmed-novel-coronavirus-case-in-india-1641593-2020-01-30|accessdate=30 January 2020|publisher=indiatoday.com|location=India|date=30 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130082158/https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/kerala-reports-first-confirmed-novel-coronavirus-case-in-india-1641593-2020-01-30|archive-date=30 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Philippines confirms its first case of coronavirus in a female Chinese national who arrived in [[Manila]] via [[Hong Kong]] on 21 January.<ref>{{cite news|title=Philippines confirms first case of novel coronavirus|url=https://cnnphilippines.com/news/2020/1/30/Philippines-coronavirus-case.html|accessdate=30 January 2020|publisher=cnnphilippines.com|location=Philippines|date=30 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130090313/https://www.cnnphilippines.com/news/2020/1/30/Philippines-coronavirus-case.html|archive-date=30 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\nJapan confirms three more cases, bringing the total to 14.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www3.nhk.or.jp/news/html/20200130/k10012266331000.html|title=\u65b0\u578b\u80ba\u708e \u56fd\u5185\u611f\u67d3\u800514\u4eba\u306b \u65b0\u305f\u306b\u7537\u5973\uff13\u4eba\u611f\u67d3\u78ba\u8a8d|date=2020-01-30|website=[[NHK]]|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201165246/https://www3.nhk.or.jp/news/html/20200130/k10012266331000.html?utm_int=news-new_contents_list-items_091|archive-date=2020-02-01|url-status=dead|language=jp}}</ref>\nMalaysia confirms one more case, bringing the total to eight.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nst.com.my/news/nation/2020/01/560955/another-chinese-national-tests-positive-2019-ncov|title=Another Chinese national tests positive for 2019-nCoV|last=Harun|first=Hana Naz|date=2020-01-30|website=NST Online|language=en|access-date=2020-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130072527/https://www.nst.com.my/news/nation/2020/01/560955/another-chinese-national-tests-positive-2019-ncov|archive-date=2020-01-30|url-status=live}}</ref> Singapore confirms three more cases, bringing the total to 13.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/wuhan-virus-singapore-new-confirmed-cases-13-12369838|title=Wuhan virus: 3 new cases confirmed in Singapore, bringing tally to 13|date=30 January 2020|website=CNA|accessdate=30 January 2020}}</ref> South Korea confirms two more cases, with one of them being the first human-to-human transmission there.<ref>{{cite web|title=S. Korea reports 2 more cases of new coronavirus, 1st human transmission|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20200130000905|website=The Korea Herald|accessdate=30 January 2020|language=en|date=30 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130153554/http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20200130000905|archive-date=30 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Vietnam confirms three new cases, bringing the total to five.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://vietnamnews.vn/society/591638/first-vietnamese-citizens-test-positive-for-coronavirus.html|title=First Vietnamese citizens test positive for coronavirus|date=2020-01-30|website=vietnamnews.vn|accessdate=2020-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130143813/https://vietnamnews.vn/society/591638/first-vietnamese-citizens-test-positive-for-coronavirus.html|archive-date=2020-01-30|url-status=live}}</ref> France confirms its sixth case.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.france24.com/en/20200130-france-confirms-sixth-case-of-coronavirus-infection-health-official-says|title=France confirms sixth case of coronavirus infection, health official says|date=2020-01-30|website=France 24|language=en|access-date=2020-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131023111/https://www.france24.com/en/20200130-france-confirms-sixth-case-of-coronavirus-infection-health-official-says|archive-date=2020-01-31|url-status=live}}</ref> Italy confirms its first two cases in a press conference by the Prime Minister, [[Giuseppe Conte]].<ref name=\"auto4\">{{cite web|url=http://news.trust.org/item/20200130210003-wm57y/|title=Two first coronavirus cases confirmed in Italy - prime minister|last=Foundation|first=Thomson Reuters|website=news.trust.org|access-date=2020-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201155938/http://news.trust.org/item/20200130210003-wm57y/|archive-date=2020-02-01|url-status=live}}</ref> Germany confirms its fifth case, an employee of the company where the four previously known cases are also employed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stmgp.bayern.de/presse/aktuelle-informationen-zur-coronavirus-lage-in-bayern-bayerisches-gesundheitsministerium-1/|title=Aktuelle Informationen zur Coronavirus-Lage in Bayern - Bayerisches Gesundheitsministerium: Ein neuer Fall im Landkreis Traunstein best\u00e4tigt|date=2020-01-30|website=Bayerisches Staatsministerium f\u00fcr Gesundheit und Pflege|language=de-DE|access-date=2020-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131030029/https://www.stmgp.bayern.de/presse/aktuelle-informationen-zur-coronavirus-lage-in-bayern-bayerisches-gesundheitsministerium-1/|archive-date=2020-01-31|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe United States confirmed its sixth case, the spouse of another patient in Chicago.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/health/health-news/coronavirus-spreads-first-time-u-s-cdc-says-n1126566|title=Coronavirus spreads for first time in U.S., CDC says|website=www.nbcnews.com|access-date=2020-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130174627/https://www.nbcnews.com/health/health-news/coronavirus-spreads-first-time-u-s-cdc-says-n1126566|archive-date=2020-01-30|url-status=live}}</ref> This is the first confirmed case of human to human transmission within the United States.  Mr. Azar, Dr. Redfield and Dr. Anthony S. Fauci agreed that a ban on travel from the epidemic\u2019s center could buy some time to put into place prevention and testing measures.  Dr. Redfield said in an interview that \u201cThere was so much we didn\u2019t know about this virus,\u201d\u201cWe were rapidly understanding it was much more transmissible, that it had a great ability to go global.\u201d <ref name=\":1\" />\n\n===31 January===\n'''WHO''' Situation Report 11:<ref>{{Citation|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200131-sitrep-11-ncov.pdf?sfvrsn=de7c0f7_4|title=Novel Coronavirus(2019-nCoV) Situation Report - 11}}</ref>\n\nThe [[United Kingdom]] and [[Russia]] confirmed their first coronavirus infections.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2020/01/31/coronavirus-symptoms-britain-russia-who-wuhan-emergency/4620574002/|title=Britain, Russia report first cases of coronavirus as illness spreads to 20 countries|first=Doug|last=Stanglin|website=USA TODAY|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206103724/https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2020/01/31/coronavirus-symptoms-britain-russia-who-wuhan-emergency/4620574002/|archive-date=2020-02-06|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-51325192|title=Coronavirus: Two cases confirmed in UK|accessdate=31 January 2020|website=BBC|date=31 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131100345/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-51325192|archive-date=31 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The first Swedish and Spanish cases were confirmed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/a/GGgL49|title=F\u00f6rsta bekr\u00e4ftade fallet av coronavirus i Sverige \u2013 kvinna h\u00e5lls isolerad|website=Aftonbladet|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201052456/https://www.aftonbladet.se/a/GGgL49|archive-date=2020-02-01|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.yahoo.com/news/spain-confirms-first-case-coronavirus-222027208.html|title=Spain Confirms First Case of Coronavirus|website=Yahoo|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131232132/https://www.yahoo.com/news/spain-confirms-first-case-coronavirus-222027208.html|archive-date=2020-01-31|url-status=live}}</ref> The seventh confirmed case in the U.S. is in [[Santa Clara County, California]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://abc7news.com/5895060/|title=LIVE: Coronavirus: Bay Area's 1st case confirmed in Santa Clara County, CDC says|date=2020-01-31|website=ABC7 San Francisco|language=en|access-date=2020-01-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131215242/https://abc7news.com/5895060/|archive-date=2020-01-31|url-status=live}}</ref> A fourth case of coronavirus in Canada has been confirmed in [[London, Ontario|London]], Ontario.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gunn |first1=Frank |title=Coronavirus updates: Third case of coronavirus confirmed in London, Ont., bringing Canadian cases to four |url=https://nationalpost.com/news/world/coronavirus-live-updates-wuhan-virus-china-2019ncov |website=National Post |publisher=The Canadian Press |language=en-CA |date=31 January 2020}}</ref> Thailand confirmed five more cases with the first human-to-human virus transmission inside the country of a local taxi driver, bringing the total to 19.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/wuhan-virus-thailand-first-human-coronavirus-transmission-12374356|title=Thailand confirms first human-to-human coronavirus transmission, total cases rises to 19|accessdate=28 January 2020|website=CNA|date=31 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131102023/https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/wuhan-virus-thailand-first-human-coronavirus-transmission-12374356|archive-date=31 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bangkokpost.com/thailand/general/1847884|title=Human transmission of coronavirus confirmed in Thailand|accessdate=28 January 2020|website=Bangkok Post|date=31 January 2020}}</ref> Singapore confirmed three more cases, bringing the total to 16.<ref>{{cite web|title=Singaporean evacuated from Wuhan among country's 3 new cases of coronavirus, total now 16: MOH|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/wuhan-virus-singapore-new-cases-coronavirus-china-12373156|website=CNA|accessdate=3 February 2020|date=31 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201130127/https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/wuhan-virus-singapore-new-cases-coronavirus-china-12373156|archive-date=1 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Chinese health experts warn the public that coronavirus patients can become reinfected. China starts repatriating citizens to [[Wuhan]].<ref name=\":15\">{{cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/society/article/3048320/china-coronavirus-deadly-day-hubei-record-high-42-patients-die|title=Coronavirus: Chinese health experts warn patients can get reinfected|date=31 January 2020|website=South China Morning Post|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200205130515/https://www.scmp.com/news/china/society/article/3048320/china-coronavirus-deadly-day-hubei-record-high-42-patients-die|archive-date=5 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nA senior leader at US Department of Health and Human Services said staff members were sent to Travis Air Force Base and March Air Reserve Base in late January and early February and were ordered to enter quarantined areas were not provided with proper safety-protocol training or equipment, with at least one person staying in a nearby hotel and leaving California on a commercial flight. <ref>{{Cite news|last=Cochrane|first=Emily|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/27/us/politics/coronavirus-us-whistleblower.html|title=U.S. Health Workers Responding to Coronavirus Lacked Training and Protective Gear, Whistle-Blower Says|date=2020-02-27|website=[[The New York Times]]|access-date=2020-04-14|last2=Weiland|first2=Noah|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331|last3=Sanger-Katz|first3=Margot}}</ref>\n\nUS bans the entry of foreign nationals who had been to China in the previous 14 days.\n\n== Events, reactions, and measures in mainland China ==\n====20 December 2019====\nOn {{date|2019-12-20}}, Winner Medical Group decided to cancel their executive meeting in Hubei.<ref>{{cite web |author1=\u7a33\u5065\u533b\u7597\u7528\u54c1\u80a1\u4efd\u6709\u9650\u516c\u53f8 |title=\u7a33\u5065\u533b\u7597\u7528\u54c1\u80a1\u4efd\u6709\u9650\u516c\u53f8 |url=http://www.winnermedical.cn/cn/newsdetail/106/666.html |website=www.winnermedical.cn |language=zh-cn |date=27 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n====30\u201331 December====\n\nOn {{date|2019-12-30}}, an \"urgent notice on the treatment of pneumonia of unknown cause\" was issued by the Medical Administration and Medical Administration of Wuhan Municipal Health Committee.<ref name=\"promed30dec\">{{cite web|title=UNDIAGNOSED PNEUMONIA \u2013 CHINA (HUBEI): REQUEST FOR INFORMATION. Archive Number: 20191230.6864153|url=https://promedmail.org/promed-post/?id=6864153|website=Pro-MED-mail|publisher=International Society for Infectious Diseases|accessdate=19 January 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"healthcomm\">{{cite web|author1=Wuhan Health Committee|url=https://www.nchrd.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/%E5%85%B3%E4%BA%8E%E5%81%9A%E5%A5%BD%E4%B8%8D%E6%98%8E%E5%8E%9F%E5%9B%A0%E8%82%BA%E7%82%8E%E6%95%91%E6%B2%BB%E5%B7%A5%E4%BD%9C%E7%9A%84%E7%B4%A7%E6%80%A5%E9%80%9A%E7%9F%A5.pdf|website=Chinese Human Rights Defenders|accessdate=14 February 2020|language=zh|title=\u5173\u4e8e\u505a\u597d\u4e0d\u660e\u539f\u56e0\u80ba\u708e\u6551\u6cbb\u5de5\u4f5c\u7684\u6025\u901a\u77e5|archive-url=https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:%E5%85%B3%E4%BA%8E%E5%81%9A%E5%A5%BD%E4%B8%8D%E6%98%8E%E5%8E%9F%E5%9B%A0%E8%82%BA%E7%82%8E%E6%95%91%E6%B2%BB%E5%B7%A5%E4%BD%9C%E7%9A%84%E7%B4%A7%E6%80%A5%E9%80%9A%E7%9F%A5.pdf|archive-date=26 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe Wuhan Municipal Health Commission also made a public announcement regarding the situation.<ref name=\":5\" />\n\nA famous police officer in [[Jiangning District]], [[Nanjing]] mentioned the BSL-4 laboratory of [[Wuhan Institute of Virology]] when commenting on the outbreak by expressing confidence on its technological power and ability to fix the incident.<ref>{{cite web |author1=\u738b\u6d77\u4e01 |authorlink1=:zh:\u738b\u6d77\u4e01 |title=\u6b66\u6c49\u8fd9\u4e2a\u4e8b\u513f\u5427\uff0c\u8981\u91cd\u89c6\u4f46\u4e0d\u8981\u6050\u614c\u3002\u56fe\u4e8c\u6700 - \u5185\u5bb9\u795e\u5668 |url=http://www.5ce.com/view/weibo/335e5de2-832b-ea11-8da2-20040ff9d71d |website=5CE.COM |archiveurl=https://archive.vn/20200301195009/http://www.5ce.com/view/weibo/335e5de2-832b-ea11-8da2-20040ff9d71d#selection-253.0-253.10 |archivedate=1 March 2020 |language=zh-cn |date=2019-12-31 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n====1 January 2020====\nHuanan Seafood Wholesale Market, the source of the initial pneumonia cases, was closed on {{date|2020-01-01}} for cleaning and disinfection.<ref name=\"promedmail\" /> On the same day, Chinese state news reported that Wuhan police interviewed eight residents for spreading \"misinformation\" referring to the new infection as another SARS and \"exaggerating\" the danger.<ref>{{cite web |title=8\u4eba\u6563\u5e03\u4e0d\u5b9e\u6d88\u606f\u88ab\u6b66\u6c49\u516c\u5b89\u67e5\u5904 \u80e1\u9521\u8fdb\u900f\u9732\u5185\u60c5 |url=https://news.sina.cn/gn/2020-01-22/detail-iihnzhha4048890.d.html |website=news.sina.cn |language=zh-cn |date=22 January 2020}}</ref> However, [[CNA (news channel)|CNA]] reported on the same date that Wuhan police said they had punished eight people for \"publishing or forwarding false information on the internet without verification.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/china-rules-out-sars-in-mystery-viral-pneumonia-outbreak-12235422|title=China rules out SARS in mystery viral pneumonia outbreak|website=CNA|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200106164940/https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/china-rules-out-sars-in-mystery-viral-pneumonia-outbreak-12235422|archive-date=2020-01-06|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn {{date|2020-01-01}}, a genetic sequencing company was notified by the Wuhan Municipal Health Committee that further sequencing of novel coronavirus samples were no longer allowed, existing samples must be destroyed and all data must be kept secret.<ref name=\"caixintrace\" />\n\n====2 January====\nOn {{date|2020-01-02}}, [[Central Hospital of Wuhan]] banned its staffs from discussing the disease publicly or recording them using text or image that can be used as evidence; situation of individual patients can only be mentioned verbally when doctors change shift.<ref>{{cite web |author1=\u675c\u73ae |title=\u4eb2\u5386\u8005\u8bb2\u8ff0\uff1a\u6b66\u6c49\u5e02\u4e2d\u5fc3\u533b\u9662\u533b\u62a4\u4eba\u5458\u88ab\u611f\u67d3\u59cb\u672b |url=https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/1zNY2YXy75snzwX3Tg09Cg |website=mp.weixin.qq.com |publisher=\u4e2d\u56fd\u65b0\u95fb\u5468\u520a |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200217184406/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/1zNY2YXy75snzwX3Tg09Cg |archivedate=17 February 2020 |language=zh |date=17 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n====3 January====\nOn {{date|2020-01-03}}, China's National Health Committee Office published an announcement classifying the novel coronavirus as a highly pathogenic microorganisms (type 2), and request all the samples to be handed to provincial or higher level health authority, other organization or person with the virus sample should either destroy or transfer them and keep the log, and emphasis that all data must be kept secret and prior approval from the authority will be needed before any results can be published.<ref name=\"caixintrace\" />\n\n====7 January====\nOn {{date|2020-01-07}}, Chinese [[Paramount leader]] and [[Communist Party of China|Party]] [[General Secretary of the Communist Party of China|general secretary]] [[Xi Jinping]] raised demand on the prevention and control of the pneumonia epidemic caused by novel coronavirus in Wuhan in a [[Politburo Standing Committee of the Communist Party of China]] meeting, according to article published by himself in February.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.yahoo.co.jp/byline/endohomare/20200216-00163380/|website=Yahoo! Japan News|date=16 February 2020|title=\u7fd2\u8fd1\u5e73\u300c1\u67087\u65e5\u306b\u611f\u67d3\u5bfe\u7b56\u6307\u793a\u300d\u306f\u865a\u507d\u304b|language=jp|author=\u9060\u85e4\u8a89}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/02/17/asia/china-coronavirus-xi-jinping-intl-hnk/index.html|title=Did Xi Jinping know about the coronavirus outbreak earlier than first suggested?|date=17 February 2020|website=CNN|first=James|last=Griffiths}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author1=\u6768\u4e9a\u6f9c |author2=\u59da\u831c |title=\u4e00\u6761\u65f6\u95f4\u8f74\u7eb5\u89c8\u4e60\u8fd1\u5e73\u7684\u6218\u201c\u75ab\u201d\u65e5\u5fd7--\u72ec\u5bb6\u7a3f\u4ef6-\u4eba\u6c11\u7f51 |url=http://cpc.people.com.cn/n1/2020/0216/c164113-31589205.html |website=www.cpnews.cn |language=zh-cn |date=17 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n====10 January====\nThe gene sequencing data of the isolated 2019-nCoV, a virus from the same family as the SARS coronavirus, was posted on Virological.org by researchers from [[Shanghai Public Health Clinical Center]] and [[Fudan University]], Shanghai. A further three sequences from the [[Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention]], one from the [[Peking Union Medical College|Chinese Academy of Medical Sciences]], and one from [[Jinyintan Hospital]] in Wuhan were posted to the Global Initiative on Sharing All Influenza Data ([[GISAID]]) portal.<ref name=\"Schnirring13Jan2020\" /><ref name=\"Schnirring11Jan2020\" /><ref name=\"Gan9Jan2020\" /><ref name=\"NCBI\" /> The same day, [[Public Health England]] issued its guidance.<ref name=\"Schnirring10Jan2020\" />\n\nBeginning of the 2020 [[Chunyun]] travel season in China.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gov.cn/xinwen/2019-12/26/content_5464103.htm|date=2019-12-26|title=2020\u5e74\u6625\u8fd0\u4ece1\u670810\u65e5\u5f00\u59cb|work=[[People's Daily]]}}</ref>\n\n====12 January====\nHubei's provincial representatives from all over the province met in Wuhan until 18 January.<ref>{{cite web |author1=\u6e56\u5317\u65e5\u62a5 |title=\u7701\u5341\u4e09\u5c4a\u4eba\u5927\u4e09\u6b21\u4f1a\u8bae\u95ed\u5e55 \u6279\u51c6\u653f\u5e9c\u5de5\u4f5c\u62a5\u544a\u7b49 \u8868\u51b3\u901a\u8fc7\u300a\u6e56\u5317\u7701\u4e61\u6751\u632f\u5174\u4fc3\u8fdb\u6761\u4f8b\u300b |url=http://m.cnhubei.com/content/2020-01/18/content_12627775.html |website=m.cnhubei.com |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129162758/http://m.cnhubei.com/content/2020-01/18/content_12627775.html |archivedate=29 January 2020 |language=zh |date=18 January 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nShanghai Public Health Clinical Center, the facility that published the first genome sequence of the virus, was closed without reason.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/society/article/3052966/chinese-laboratory-first-shared-coronavirus-genome-world-ordered|title=Chinese laboratory that first shared coronavirus genome with world ordered to close for 'rectification', hindering its Covid-19 research|first=Zhuang|last=Pinghui|date=28 February 2020|work=South China Morning Post}}</ref>\n\n====14 January====\nReporters from Hong Kong being taken to police station after trying to film situation within Wuhan hospital.<ref>{{cite news|work=RTHK|url=https://news.rthk.hk/rthk/ch/component/k2/1502706-20200114.htm|title=\u6b66\u6f22\u6536\u6cbb\u80ba\u708e\u60a3\u8005\u91ab\u9662\u5b88\u885b\u68ee\u56b4\u3000\u672c\u6e2f\u8a18\u8005\u88ab\u5e36\u5230\u6d3e\u51fa\u6240|date=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n====15 January====\nRepresentative from Chinese government and American government sign the [[US\u2013China Phase One trade deal|phase one trade deal]] over bilateral trade conflict in Washington D.C.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Wearden |first1=Graeme |title=US and China sign Phase One trade deal, but experts are sceptical - business live |url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/live/2020/jan/15/us-china-trade-deal-trump-tariffs-global-risks-uk-inflation-business-live?page=with:block-5e1f53fe8f0852212f74eabc#block-5e1f53fe8f0852212f74eabc |website=The Guardian |date=15 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Donnan |first1=Shawn |last2=Wingrove |first2=Josh |last3=Mohsin |first3=Saleha |title=U.S. and China Sign Phase One of Trade Deal |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-01-15/u-s-china-sign-phase-one-of-trade-deal-trump-calls-remarkable |website=Bloomberg |date=15 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n====20 January====\nChina's National Health Commission announced confirmation that the coronavirus had begun to be transmitted between humans.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2020-01/20/c_138721762.htm|title=China confirms human-to-human transmission of 2019-nCoV, infection of medical staff|work=Xinhua|date=20 January 2020|access-date=8 April 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200121183816/http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2020-01/20/c_138721762.htm|archivedate=21 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nChinese premier [[Li Keqiang]] urged decisive and effective efforts to prevent and control the epidemic.<ref name=\"Premier urged2\" /> Beijing and Guangdong reported an additional three and thirteen laboratory-confirmed cases, respectively. Shanghai confirms its first case, bringing the total number of laboratory-confirmed cases in China to 218.<ref name=\"strait20jan\" /><ref name=\":6\" />\n\n====22 January====\nThe government announced a quarantine until further notice, cancelling outgoing flights and trains from Wuhan, and suspending public transportation in Wuhan, effective 10:00 (02:00 [[Coordinated Universal Time|UTC]], [[UTC+08:00]]) on 23 January.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/01/22/world/asia/china-coronavirus-travel.html|title=Wuhan, Center of Coronavirus Outbreak, Is Cut Off by Chinese Authorities|newspaper=The New York Times|access-date=2020-01-22|date=22 January 2020|last1=Qin|first1=Amy|last2=Wang|first2=Vivian}}</ref> However, statistics compiled by the [[National Railway Administration|Chinese Railway Administration]] showed that on the same day approximately 100,000 people had already departed from Wuhan Train Station by the deadline.<ref name=\"Wuhan\">{{cite web|url=https://news.ltn.com.tw/news/world/breakingnews/3048974|title=\u6b66\u6f22\u80ba\u708e\u300b\u9ad8\u8abf\u300c#\u9003\u96e2\u6b66\u6f22\u300d \u5c01\u57ce\u524d\u5915\u81f3\u5c1130\u842c\u4eba\u9003\u51fa - \u570b\u969b|date=2020-01-23|website=\u81ea\u7531\u96fb\u5b50\u5831|language=zh|access-date=2020-01-23}}</ref> Furthermore, many Wuhan residents bypassed the checkpoints by taking [[antipyretic]]s, having seen tips shared on [[Sina Weibo]].<ref name=\"Wuhan\" />\n\nAt the day's night, Wuhan government announced that citizens must wear [[face mask (disambiguation)|face mask]] in public facilities.<ref>{{cite news|language=zh|url=https://chinadigitaltimes.net/chinese/2020/02/%E4%B8%AD%E5%9B%BD%E6%96%B0%E9%97%BB%E5%91%A8%E5%88%8A%E8%A2%AB%E5%88%A0%E5%B0%81%E9%9D%A2%E6%96%87%E7%AB%A0%EF%BD%9C%E6%AD%A6%E6%B1%89%E4%B9%8B%E6%86%BE%EF%BC%9A%E9%BB%84%E9%87%91%E9%98%B2%E6%8E%A7/|author=\u4e1c\u683c|date=2020-02-11|work=China Digital Times|trans-title=China News Weekly's deleted cover article {{!}} 'Li Xiangyi; Li Mingzi; Peng Dani; Du Wei (2020-02-10) \"The Regret of Wuhan: How China Missed the Critical Window for Controlling the Coronavirus Outbreak\" China News Weekly Issue 934'|title=\u4e2d\u56fd\u65b0\u95fb\u5468\u520a\u88ab\u5220\u5c01\u9762\u6587\u7ae0 {{!}} '\u674e\u60f3\u4fe3; \u674e\u660e\u5b50; \u5f6d\u4e39\u59ae; \u675c\u73ae 2020.2.10 \"\u6b66\u6c49\u4e4b\u61be\uff1a\u9ec4\u91d1\u9632\u63a7\u671f\u662f\u5982\u4f55\u9519\u8fc7\u7684\uff1f\" \u671f\u300a\u4e2d\u56fd\u65b0\u95fb\u5468\u520a\u300b \u603b\u7b2c 934'}}</ref>\n\n====23 January====\nWuhan [[2020 Wuhan lockdown|suspended all public transportation]] from 10 a.m. onwards, including all bus, metro and ferry lines. Additionally, all outbound trains and flights were halted.<ref name=\":7\" /> In Wuhan, construction began near midnight for a [[Huoshenshan Hospital|specialist emergency hospital]], modelled after the [[Xiaotangshan Hospital]] during the [[SARS outbreak|2003 SARS outbreak]] in Beijing, after it was proposed earlier in the afternoon. The new [[Huoshenshan Hospital]] opened on 3 February with a capacity of at least 1,000 beds.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.people.cn/n3/2020/0124/c90000-9651671.html|title=Wuhan to follow Beijing's SARS treatment model in new coronavirus control - People's Daily Online|website=en.people.cn|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200124140742/http://en.people.cn/n3/2020/0124/c90000-9651671.html|archive-date=2020-01-24|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe three provinces of Zhejiang,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/3906959.html|title=\u6d59\u6c5f\u51b3\u5b9a\u542f\u52a8\u91cd\u5927\u516c\u5171\u7a81\u53d1\u536b\u751f\u4e8b\u4ef6\u4e00\u7ea7\u54cd\u5e94{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=24 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129211550/https://www.jiemian.com/article/3906959.html|archive-date=29 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Guangdong,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/3908009.html|title=\u5e7f\u4e1c\u7701\u51b3\u5b9a\u542f\u52a8\u91cd\u5927\u7a81\u53d1\u516c\u5171\u536b\u751f\u4e8b\u4ef6\u4e00\u7ea7\u54cd\u5e94{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=24 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129211546/https://www.jiemian.com/article/3908009.html|archive-date=29 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> and Hunan<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/3908499.html|title=\u6e56\u5357\u7701\u51b3\u5b9a\u542f\u52a8\u91cd\u5927\u7a81\u53d1\u516c\u5171\u536b\u751f\u4e8b\u4ef6\u4e00\u7ea7\u54cd\u5e94{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=24 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129211548/https://www.jiemian.com/article/3908499.html|archive-date=29 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> declared a level 1 public health emergency (the highest possible) in chronological order.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.guancha.cn/politics/2020_01_24_532969.shtml|title=9\u7701\u5e02\u542f\u52a8\u4e00\u7ea7\u54cd\u5e94 (Nine Provinces and Municipalities Enact Level 1 Responses)|last=|first=|date=24 January 2020|website=Guancha.cn|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200124100026/https://www.guancha.cn/politics/2020_01_24_532969.shtml|archive-date=24 January 2020|access-date=24 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe release of all seven major films for the Lunar New Year was practically cancelled.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://money.163.com/20/0124/07/F3KV962700259DLP.html|title=\u98ce\u4e91\u7a81\u53d8\uff1a\u4e03\u90e8\u5f71\u7247\u5168\u90e8\u5ba3\u5e03\u64a4\u6863 \u4eca\u5e74\u5df2\u65e0\u6625\u8282\u6863|last=\u7f51\u6613|date=24 January 2020|website=money.163.com|access-date=24 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200124052130/https://money.163.com/20/0124/07/F3KV962700259DLP.html|archive-date=24 January 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> In an example of [[black humor]], ''[[Plague Inc.]]'', which was released in 2012, surged to become the most popular app in China.<ref name=\"Plague, Inc.\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/technology-51222796|title=Killer plague game tops charts amid coronavirus|date=23 January 2020|website=BBC News|access-date=24 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200123230821/https://www.bbc.com/news/technology-51222796|archive-date=23 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n====24 January====\nThe seven provinces, two autonomous regions, and all four municipalities of Hubei,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/3909372.html|title=\u6e56\u5317\u7701\u542f\u52a8\u91cd\u5927\u7a81\u53d1\u516c\u5171\u536b\u751f\u4e8b\u4ef6\u4e00\u7ea7\u54cd\u5e94{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=24 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200125072914/https://www.jiemian.com/article/3909372.html|archive-date=25 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Anhui,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/3909516.html|title=\u5b89\u5fbd\u542f\u52a8\u91cd\u5927\u516c\u5171\u536b\u751f\u4e8b\u4ef6\u4e00\u7ea7\u54cd\u5e94{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=24 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200125072916/https://www.jiemian.com/article/3909516.html|archive-date=25 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Tianjin,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/3909529.html|title=\u5929\u6d25\u5e02\u542f\u52a8\u5e94\u5bf9\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u611f\u67d3\u7684\u80ba\u708e\u4e00\u7ea7\u54cd\u5e94{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=24 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200125072911/https://www.jiemian.com/article/3909529.html|archive-date=25 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Beijing,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/3909690.html|title=\u5317\u4eac\u786e\u8bca\u75c5\u4f8b29\u4eba\uff0c\u542f\